President Trump held a press conference in the Oval Office to celebrate the return of Danny Burch, an American citizen who was held captive in Yemen for over 18 months. The President thanked the United Arab Emirates (UAE) and other allies for their help in securing Burch's release. Vice President Mike Pence, Senator Mitt Romney, and Senator Lindsey Graham were also present at the press conference. They praised the President's commitment to bringing Americans home from captivity and expressed their support for his efforts. The President also mentioned ongoing negotiations for the release of other hostages, but did not provide specific details. The press conference concluded with brief comments about trade talks with China and concerns about North Korea's reported rebuilding of a missile launch site. The President stated that he would be disappointed if the reports were true and emphasized the need to solve the problem with North Korea.